thread.title: Spotify's Top 10 most streamed tracks
thread.title_full: Spotify's Top 10 most streamed tracks - Yahoo News

author: The Associated Press
title: Spotify's Top 10 most streamed tracks
text:
The following list represents the most streamed tracks on Spotify, based on the number of people who shared it divided by the number who listened to it, from Friday Oct. 9 to Thursday, Oct. 15, via Facebook, Tumblr, Twitter and Spotify.
UNITED STATES
1. Drake, "Hotline Bling" (Cash Money Records Inc.)
2. The Weeknd, "The Hills" (Republic Records)
3. Justin Bieber, "What Do You Mean?" (Def Jam Recordings)
4. Drake, Future, "Jumpman" (Cash Money Records Inc.)
5. The Weeknd, "Can't Feel My Face" (Republic Records)
6. Fetty Wap, "679 (feat. Remy Boyz)" (300 Entertainment)
7. Shawn Mendes, "Stitches" (Island Records)
8. Selena Gomez, "Good For You" (Interscope Records)
9. Fetty Wap, "Trap Queen" (300 Entertainment)
10. Fetty Wap, "Again" (300 Entertainment)
UNITED KINGDOM
1. Justin Bieber, "What Do You Mean?" (Def Jam Recordings)
2. Drake, "Hotline Bling" (Cash Money Records Inc.)
3. Sigala, "Easy Love - Original Mix" (Ministry of Sound Recordings)
4. The Weeknd, "Can't Feel My Face" (Republic Records)
5. R. City , "Locked Away" (Kemosabe Records)
6. Calvin Harris, Disciples, "How Deep Is Your Love" (Sony Music Entertainment UK Limited)
7. Ellie Goulding, "On My Mind" (Polydor Ltd.)
8. Pia Mia, "Do It Again" (Interscope Records)
9. The Weeknd, "The Hills" (Republic Records)
10. Macklemore & Ryan Lewis, "Downtown" (Macklemore, LLC)
GLOBAL
1. Justin Bieber, "What Do You Mean?" (Def Jam Recordings)
2. The Weeknd, "Can't Feel My Face" (Republic Records)
3. Drake, "Hotline Bling" (Cash Money Records Inc.)
4. The Weeknd, "The Hills" (Republic Records)
5. R. City , "Locked Away" (Kemosabe Records)
6. Major Lazer, "Lean On (feat. MØ & DJ Snake)" (Mad Decent)
7. Calvin Harris, Disciples, "How Deep Is Your Love" (Sony Music Entertainment UK Limited)
8. Shawn Mendes, "Stitches" (Island Records)
9. Ellie Goulding, "On My Mind" (Polydor Ltd.)
10. Selena Gomez, "Good For You" (Interscope Records)
